THE ORGANIZATION HAS A CONTRACT WITH THE CITY OF AMARILLO TO BE THE FISCAL AGENT FOR THE ORGANIZATION AND TO PROVIDE THE FOLLOWING SERVICES: PREPARATION OF DISBURSEMENT CHECKS, HUMAN RESOURCES AND PAYROLL PROCESSING, MAINTENANCE OF GENERAL LEDGER AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, AND CASH MANAGEMENT FUNCTIONS.
THE ORGANIZATION HAS MEMBERS WHICH PAY MEMBERSHIP FEES BASED ON THE SIZE OF THE ORGANIZATION.
THE MEMBERSHIP ELECTS MEMBERS TO THE GOVERNING BOARD OF DIRECTORS.
THE FORM 990 AND 990T IS REVIEWED WITH THE PRESIDENT AND VP OF FINANCE AND ADMINISTRATION, AND THEN WITH THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE BEFORE FILING.
EMPLOYEES SIGN STATEMENT IN EMPLOYEE HANDBOOK WHICH STATES THAT THEY HAVE READ THE POLICY.

ANNUALLY, THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE PERFORMS A SALARY REVIEW OF THE PRESIDENT AND OTHER OFFICERS USING COMPARABLE DATA FROM AMERICAN CHAMBER OF COMMERCE SALARY SERVICES, TEXAS ASSOCIATION OF BUSINESS SALARY SERVICES, OTHER CHAMBERS, AND EXECUTIVE SALARIES IN THE COMMUNITY. THE SALARY IS REFLECTED IN THE APPROVED ANNUAL BUDGET.
